\[ f(x) = \begin{cases} 
2\{x\} - 1 & \text{if } 0 \leq \{x\} < \frac{1}{2} \\
1 - 2\{x\} & \text{if } \frac{1}{2} \leq \{x\} < 1 
\end{cases} \]
Next, we need to determine the value of \( f(xf(x)) \). Since \(f(x)\) ranges from 0 to 1, we need to consider the values of \(f(y)\) for \(0 \leq y \leq 1\):
\[ f(y) = \begin{cases} 
2y - 1 & \text{if } 0 \leq y < \frac{1}{2} \\
1 - 2y & \text{if } \frac{1}{2} \leq y \leq 1 
\end{cases} \]
